features: Your clothes will love sheets - we made this liquid free detergent sheet to soften and reduce wrinkles and eliminate odors, stains, and dirt. Our high efficiency laundry detergent sheet is ideal for everyday laundry cleaning, including cottons, linens, blends, and durable synthetics. It's also safe for whites and all colors, and you can use it in hot, cold, hard, or soft water. Great for the earth.

Long lasting detergent sheet that's safe for you - our powerful concentrated laundry detergent sheet is formulated to last 3 years and is also made without harsh ingredients, making it safe for you and your clothes. Our laundry sheet is eco-friendly, plastic free with recyclable packaging, we are please to say it's septic safe and is he compatible. A tru clean

Sheets easy to use 1 sheet and go application gives you the right amount-every time. Just drop 1 sheets from our recyclable box into the washer and you're done. Uses no Dyes, or artificial brighteners. Compatible with front and top loading, high efficiency washing machine.
Dissolves completely in hot or cold water, powerful cleaning. Eco-responsible packaging, biodegradable, dye free, natural, septic safe, vegan. Momtastic Says "Mommy Must Have".

Much like our detergent sheets, our dryer sheets are also eco-friendly. They soften and reduce the static on your clothes with proprietary plant-based softening agents. They are fragranced with our special blend of essential oils. Our dryer sheets provide a natural softening and freshening experience while offering the ruggedness of a more traditional type dryer sheet that won’t shred in the dryer like competing paper-based eco-dryer sheets.

Perfect for sensitive skin - our revolutionary formula of laundry detergent sheet is made without ingredients that are the leading causes of skin irritation, making our detergent sheet perfect for kids and adults with sensitive skin and who don't want to sacrifice fresh smelling clothes. Easy for kids to use

A deeper clean - Believe it or not, even the best detergents may not altogether remove all the body soils and stains trapped deep within items in your washload. So the clothing and bedding that looks clean it may not be. Eww! That's where Sheets comes in. It's formulated to better penetrate into and between fibers to dissolve and remove body oils and others nasties you may not even be able to see.
Up to 100 loads, for those who do extra small to small loads you can use 1/2 a sheet for a full clean. Our sheets are precut and pre-measured so you can say goodbye to overused liquid.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love the small packaging. Due to health issues it is difficult to lift and pour the large liquid containers. These little sheets do not have a strong aroma which helps to avoid my allergy flair ups. When I do hand laundry in my small sink, I use one-half sheet. Another advantage is the clothes are very easy to rinse saving time and water. The only “con” is it does not handle bad odors very well. I have kitties and I have to pre-treat the article before washing, or the kitty odor stays. All my laundry gets clean just as well as any of the liquid detergent that I have used.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love the these space savers! Most importantly the wash is clean and smells great with one sheet and the dryer sheets are also great and effective with just one sheet. I will try the lavender dryer sheets next. We are very satisfied with these products and we will continue to buy them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great For Travel
reviews.reviewText: Originally bought these after seeing them on Shark Tank, and were persuaded that it was a good thing to do for the environment. However, my wife really didn't like how they performed. But, we then had a vacation planned for a couple weeks, during which we were going to do laundry. They worked great for that. Easy to pack, easy to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great environmentally conscious product
reviews.reviewText: I love this laundry detergent sheet and the complimentary dryer sheets. The detergent foams up really nicely, dissolves quickly and completely, and gets my clothes clean. Plus, they hardly take up any space and I feel much better not throwing away huge plastic jugs. Just be sure to store them in a manner they won get wet.I absolutely adore the dryer sheets. They don’t smell chemically at all, they make my clothes super soft and smell good (I use two of the dryer sheets every time - I usually wash extra large loads), plus they’re not awful for your health and the environment like regular dryer sheets! I’m so happy I found these and will be purchasing more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Tried to eliminate liquid detergent
reviews.reviewText: Well decided I would try this and found out not only do I need more sheets to have clean clothes I also noticed it doesn't seem to be cleaning them nearly as well as the liquid. It's okay at best for me. The smell is great though lol

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I think this is a great concept. Love these and love that I don’t have to go out and buy a huge container of detergent and lug it around. I went on vacation and we had a washer/dryer. I brought these washer sheets and they were great! I actually bought them for my daughter who is going off to college. Thought I’d try them and see if they were worth shipping to her so she didn’t have to worry about storing liquid detergent - since she’s in a dorm and space is a premium. They work pretty good and love the dryer sheets. I only wish they gave you the same number of dryer sheets as washer sheets, or more. I also use dryer balls and love that my clothes don’t have that liquid detergent smell - I used to like it but it’s too much and you don’t realize that you really don’t need all that for the laundry to be clean. It’s a much lighter scent and I like it. Highly recommend if you’re looking to ditch the big bottles and want something that’s better for the environment and your skin.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2022
reviews.reviewText: When I received my package from Amazon, opened the bag and there was only 1 box. I thought someone had left something out and I sent an unhappy note to the seller. Nope. Once I got the box opened, you have to break the seal on the white label. Once the box was opened, I found 2 boxes inside, 1 for laundry sheets & 1 for dryer sheets. 3rd picture shows 1 laundry sheet ready to use.I did 2 loads of laundry. The one with clothing had a cloth hanky that had blood stains, now it doesn't. There were also cloth napkins that had food stains, now they don't. My clothing came out of the washer fresh smelling & clean. The dryer sheet made them soft, wrinkle free and smelling great! The 2nd load was a load of of towels & washcloths, clean & smelling fresh. I don't use dryer sheets when I dry my towels & sheets.Very pleased with the Sheets Laundry products. I live in senior housing and showed my neighbors the Sheets Laundry products, they were very interested. As for me, no more buy or having to lug laundry detergent in plastic upstairs!PS I contacted Sheets Laundry and let them know once I got the box opened I had both products and ignore my unhappy note ;).
